line_1: Yet will it ne'er with furious impotence
line_2: Ne'er swell with rage, nor foam with violence;

line_1: With all the rage of pedant impotence?
line_2: Still vainly scribble on with pert pretence,

line_1: Like eunuchs rage of love, from impotence.
line_2: Want of success his passion but augments;
Witlings, brisk fools, curs'd with half sense,

line_1: And Lust is yok'd to Impotence.
line_2: Wit's forc'd to Chum with Common Sense,

line_1: And Rhyme with all the Rage of Impotence!
line_2: Strain out the last, dull droppings of their Sense,

line_1: And cure ev'n age and impotence:
line_2: Nay I fresh vigour can dispense,
